HEADWORD: Excitable
<hw>Ex*cit"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>excitabilis</ets> inciting: cf. F. <ets>excitable</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Capable of being excited, or roused into action; susceptible of
excitement; easily stirred up, or stimulated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>excitableness</ent>⟦br⟧
